   COMMUNICATIONS (ICACC 2013)},
Year = {2013},
Pages = {5-8},
Note = {3rd International Conference on Advances in Computing and Communications
   (ICACC), Kochi, INDIA, AUG 29-31, 2013},
Organization = {IEEE; Rajagiri Sch Engn \& Technol; IEEE Comp Soc},
Abstract = {Due to heavy traffic the network monitoring is very difficult and
   cumbersome job, hence the probability of network attacks increases
   substantially. So there is the need of extraction anomalies. Anomaly
   extraction means to find flows associated with the anomalous events, in
   a large set of flows observed during an anomalous time interval. Anomaly
   extraction is very important for root-cause analysis, network forensics,
   attack mitigation and anomaly modeling. To identify the suspicious
   flows, we use meta-data provided by several histogram based detectors
   and then apply association rule with multidimensional mining concept to
   find and summarize anomalous flows. By taking rich traffic data from a
   backbone network, we show that our technique effectively finds the flows
   associated with the anomalous events. So by applying multidimensional
   mining rule to extract anomaly, we can reduce the work-hours needed for
   analyzing alarms and making anomaly systems more effective.},
