Abstract = {An approach to the concept of Big Data and the types of data storage
   that comprise it and the scope of Smart Data and the profiles. The
   protection and conservation of data in cases of prosecution of crime at
   Directives 95/46/EC, 2002/58/ EC, 2006/24/EC and the recent 2016/680/EC,
   as well as Regulation 2016/679/EC. The protection of natural persons
   with regard to the processing of personal data by the competent
   authorities for the purpose of prevention, investigation, detection or
   prosecution of criminal offenses or the execution of criminal sanctions,
   and free circulation of said data. Given this scenario, the possibility
   of using profiles in electronic surveillance and the new problem that
   would arise, Smart Data in general. The individual can be at the center
   of an investigation, which invades private life, including the most
   intimate one, and can compromise the presumption of innocence.
   Research and criminal surveillance has at its disposal, today
   technological means, which must be used in accordance with the
   provisions of the law to prevent interference with fundamental rights.
   These advanced investigation procedures, provided under the principles
   of specialty and proportionality, with due judicial authorization,
