   Siddhant Coll Engn, Pune, INDIA, APR 07-09, 2017},
Organization = {IEEE; Sahyadri Valley Coll Engn \& Technol; Asian Soc Sci Res; SVCET,
   Jha Sci Res Pvt Ltd},
Abstract = {In today's world data is growing very rapidly, which we call as big
   data. To deal with these large data sets, currently we are using NoSQL
   databases, as relational database is not capable for handling such data.
   These schema less NoSQL database allow us to handle unstructured data.
   Through this paper we are comparing two NoSQL databases MongoDB and
   CouchBase server, in terms of image storage and retrieval. Aim behind
   selecting these two databases as both comes under Document store
   category. Major applications like social media, traffic analysis,
   criminal database etc. require image database. The motivation behind
   this paper is to compare database performance in terms of time required
   to store and retrieve images from database. In this paper, firstly we
   are going describe advantages of NoSQL databases over SQL, then brief
   idea about MongoDB and CouchBase and finally comparison of time required
   to insert various size images in databases and to retrieve various size
   images using front end tool Java.},
