   A. and Kuznetsov, N. A. and Raigorodskii, A. M. and Trenin, S. A.},
Title = {Identification in Digital Economy Computer Systems},
Journal = {JOURNAL OF COMMUNICATIONS TECHNOLOGY AND ELECTRONICS},
Year = {2019},
Volume = {64},
Number = {12},
Pages = {1493-1499},
Month = {DEC},
Abstract = {A new method of interactive identification is proposed-trusted
   identification of a person using untrusted devices (e.g., smartphones,
   tablets, etc.). It is shown that static, unchangeable, or almost
   invariable biometric features can be used in criminology, but it is
   impractical for digital economy computer systems. It is inefficient to
   use fingerprints, iris and retina, vascular pattern, etc., as
   characteristics. On the contrary, it is necessary to use inherent human
   dynamic characteristics , for example, those manifested in reflexes. As
   such, eye movements can be used when reading and/or tracking a stimulus,
   as well as saccades, pulse wave, and others. For decision-making it is
   proposed to use artificial neural networks.},
