   (MAD), Phuket, THAILAND, JUN 10-14, 2024},
Organization = {ACM},
Abstract = {In this talk, Dang-Nguyen discusses case studies conducted in
   collaboration with fact-checkers and journalists in the Nordic
   countries, with a specific focus on the user needs of fact-checkers,
   their workflows, and tools employed for verifying visual content in news
   (see {[}1, 2]). The majority of the case study centers on examining the
   workflows and tools utilized by multiple fact-checkers at Faktisk
   (faktisk.no), a prominent Norwegian fact-checking organization. The
   discussion covers the efficacy of AI tools, geolocation services,
   internet archives, and social media monitoring platforms in facilitating
   efficient evidence processing and verification. This talk involves
   sharing experiences and interactive discussions with the audience,
   encouraging exploration of the potential benefits and current
   limitations of technology, aiming to provide insights for future
   developments in multimedia AI.},
