   IEEE Photon Soc; IEEE Robot \& Automat Soc},
Abstract = {Crime forecasting has been made possible by criminological theories and
   developments in computational techniques/data analytics further improved
   the technologies of forecasting. It helps the various departments of the
   police to make a decision and strategy to prevent the crime. This paper
   focuses on forecasting the annual crime rate in India using the Time
   Series Models such as Auto-Regressive Integrated Moving Average (ARIMA)
   and Exponential Smoothing. Source of data is from the National Crime
   Record Bureau of India. As a part of modeling, data is divided into
   training data for the years 1953 to 2008 and test data for the years
   2009 to 2013. By examining the model, it's clear that the forecast
   values are within the 95\% confidence interval of the test data and
   accuracy measurements are also significant. Hence the time series model
   suitable for crime forecasting.},
